:: 1. {"position":"100,3300","size":"100,100"}
M: - end of fight
Such boldness...

Sauntering in here so full of vigor,

So full of *life*.

A worthy adversary, all the better that your blood tastes so sweet.

PC:
I'll take that as a compliment.  [[Good]] 

Enjoy it while it lasts, now surrender. [[Neutral]]

It'll be the last you taste, you *Ghoul*[[Kill]]


:: 1.1 {"position":"500,1400","size":"100,100"}
PC: I'm reaching the core, no matter what it takes.

M: No one's been there in a thousand years.

Or has it been longer...

Who knows what you're going to find in there,

I heard the last only survived a century.

But, why do you wish to reach it?

PC: To kill it...to take it. I'll know when I'm there. [[1.1.1]]

That's none of your concern, step aside or I'll deal with you here. [[1.1.2]]


:: 1.1.1 {"position":"700,1200","size":"100,100"}
PC: I'll know when I'm there.

M: Hm.

How about we strike a deal?

I'm interested in you, so I'll help you.

Take me with you to the core,

And once we've defeated it,

Take me with you to the surface.

PC: Your strength will be a valuable asset. I accept. [[success1]]

I'm not into your kind. [[failure1]]


:: 1.1.2 {"position":"700,1500","size":"100,100"}
PC: That's none of your concern, step aside or I'll deal with you here. 

M: There's no acquiescing here.

You can try to finish me.

Or tell me why.

If you wish to kill it,

My services would be...available.

PC: ...perhaps I do wish to kill it. [[success2]]

I don't need your help. [[failure2]]




:: 1.2 {"position":"525,2100","size":"100,100"}
PC: I don't owe you an explanation.

M: You don't owe me anything.

But it has been so long since I've seen a Hunter.

Humour me, is it just to kill?

Or do you wish for more...

PC: ...more? [[1.2.1]]

Killing is the only thing on the table. [[1.2.2]]




:: 1.2.1 {"position":"700,1900","size":"100,100"}
PC: ...more? 

M: More...

Power.

The core only comes to be in one way.

Although I'm not sure how long that power would last with the Dungeon in this state.

I would quite like to see the outcome regardless.

Hunter, take me with you.

PC: ...so be it. I could use the extra...help. [[success3]]

And chance you taking it? No. [[failure3]]



:: 1.2.2 {"position":"700,2200","size":"100,100"}
PC: Killing is the only thing on the table. 

M: Of course,

Which is why I intend to help.

You're the first living being I've seen in over six decades,

Or has it been more...

Either way,

I'm sick of waiting.

Take me with you.

PC: Don't get in my way. [[success4]]

A bold demand, I decline. [[failure4]]


:: 2.1 {"position":"500,3100","size":"100,100"}
PC: You have one minute.

M: So *gracious*

You've proven your strength,

Surely you feel I've proven mine.

So let me proposition you,

I'll help you get to the core...

If you take me out of here with you.

PC: Why would you want to leave? [[2.1.1]]

You think I'm going to trust you?[[2.1.2]]


:: 2.1.1 {"position":"700,2800","size":"100,100"}
PC: Why would you want to leave?

M: You have eyes, no?

Look around.

This place doesn't have much longer left.

My chances up there are better than the definitive death that awaits me here.

PC: I suppose you could be a good distraction.[[success2.1]]

I'll be damned if I help you terrorise the surface. [[failure2.1]]


:: 2.1.2 {"position":"700,3200","size":"100,100"}
PC: You think I'm going to trust you?

M: Of course not,

I thought you'd use that pretty little head of yours,

I'm dead regardless,

So what's the loss for you?

PC: ...you're dead the second you make a wrong move[[success2.1.2.]]

I won't be taken for a fool. [[failure2.1.2]]


:: 2.2 {"position":"500,3500","size":"100,100"}
PC: I don't have time to humour you.

M: Then why exactly are you asking me to surrender?

Surely you would have just killed me by now if you weren't slightly intrigued?

So I'll ask again, 

Let me do the talking.

PC: ... [[2.2.1]]

PC: If you're that eager for me to finish the job[[2.2.2]]


:: 2.2.1 {"position":"700,3500","size":"100,100"}
PC: ...

M: Good.

*sigh*

This place is dying,

I have no intention of waiting to die with it.

I'll help you get to the core, defeat it if you so wish.

*If*, you'll bring me up to the surface.

PC: An extra hand can't hurt. [[success2.2.1]]

As if I'd believe that. [[failure2.2.1]]


:: 2.2.2 {"position":"700,4000","size":"100,100"}
PC: If you're that eager for me to finish the job.

M: Hold on!

...

This brings me no pleasure to offer my services in such a position.

But I can help you get to the core.

Just bring me to the surface when you're done.

PC: If you'd just said that to begin with. [[success2.2.2]]

PC: No chance.[[failure2.2.2.]]


:: 3.1 {"position":"500,4700","size":"100,100"}
PC: Perceptive, are we.

M: Only when someone interesting catches my eye.

Your strength is commendable,

It's been too long since I've met someone of your prowess,

You're sure to give this place a good run.

PC: You don't sound like someone who's about to die. [[3.1.1.]]

Flattery won't save you here. [[3.1.2]]


:: 3.1.1. {"position":"700,4600","size":"100,100"}
PC: You don't sound like someone who's about to die.

M: I've long accepted my death, 

I'd rather it be by the hands of a valiant fighter,

than simply wasting away here.

PC: Wasting away? [[3.1.1.1]]

Then I'll grant that. [[failure21]]


:: 3.1.1.1 {"position":"900,4500","size":"100,100"}
PC: Wasting away?

M: This dungeon won't be alive for much longer.

I know you're strong, 

You must have fought plenty of Ghouls before,

So you must feel that we, down here, aren't as we used to be

PC: Then why not leave? [[3.1.1.1.1]]

Insult my strength, I'll show you. [[failure22]]


:: 3.1.1.1.1 {"position":"1100,4400","size":"100,100"}
